The paper deals with the subword complexity of infinite words, which is a topic in discrete mathematics (cs.DM). It also involves the avoidance of certain powers in these words, which is related to formal languages (cs.FL) and information theory (cs.IT). The paper uses techniques from combinatorics (cs.CC) and numerical analysis (cs.NA) to analyze the subword complexity of different types of words.
